    <Instrument_Host>
        <name>Venera 8</name>
        <type>Spacecraft</type>
        <description>

The Venera 8 spacecraft comprised a carrier bus holding a descent
craft/lander to study Venus. The carrier bus was designed to be a
communications relay for the lander and to explore interplanetary space
during cruise and Venus approach. Instrumentation included energetic
particle detectors, solar wind detector, and UV spectrometer. 

        </description>
